title.undefined: Circular Economy Ontology Network (CEON) - Energy Module

description.undefined: A module of the CEON ontology network defining aspects of the energy concept.

coversRequirements.value: Covers the following requirements from Onto-DESIDE D3.2: CE1-2, CE4-3, CE6-3, CE7-4, CE8-2, CE10-7, CE10-9, CE11-6, CE12-5.

title.value: Circular Economy Ontology Network (CEON) - Energy Module

comment.undefined: An energy source is a resource or system that provides the energy.

comment.en: A constituent is a component of object.

comment.undefined: Biofuel is a fuel that is produced over a short time span from biomass.
The generic relation representing the particpation of a resource in some relation. For example, it can be specialized to represent a reified version of an object or data property.
Represents the participation of objects in some situation.
A digital object, e.g. a computer file, that is located on some server, hard drive, or on the web. Most often the digital object is the realization of some piece of information.

comment.en: A batch of objects is a collection of physical objects that are of the same type, e.g. a set of items (product objects) adhering to the same product model.

comment.undefined: The relation involving the role of a certain actor with respect to a certain resource, e.g. an organisation or individual (actor) owning (role) a specific product (resource) at a specific point or period in time.

The relation involving the role of a certain actor with respect to a value network or a process in such a network, e.g. an organisation (actor) acting as the recycler (role) in a glass recycling value netowrk (network) at a specific point or period in time. Or an organisation (actor) acting as the dismantler (role) in a dismantling step of a building deconstruction process (process step) at a specific point or period in time.
Solar Energy Source is the Sun.

comment.en: A set of objects is a set of physical objects (items) that can be of different types, i.e. different kinds of items.

comment.undefined: A fossil fuel is a carbon compound- or hydrocarbon-containing material[2] formed naturally in the Earth's crust from the buried remains of prehistoric organisms (animals, plants or planktons), a process that occurs within geological formations.
Something that the actor is capable of doing, e.g. perfomring a certain role in a process, based on some properties, such as access to infrastructure, resources and know-how.
The infrastructures participating in various energy-related processes, including energy production, transmission or distribution.
Geothermal Energy Source is the Earth's crust. Geothermal energy is thermal energy extracted from the Earth's crust. It combines energy from the formation of the planet and from radioactive decay.
Renewable energy represents energy that comes from renewable resources.

comment.en: Information is an abstract concept that represents any kind of interpretations. For instance, information can be data generated by software systems or data used by people for communications.

comment.undefined: Nonrenewable energy represents energy that comes from such resources that cannot be replaced onew they are used up.
Energy Conversion is a process of transforming energy.
A collaboration between a set of actors.
Biogas represents an energy source that is produced from raw materials such as agricultural waste, manure, municipal waste, plant material, sewage, green waste, wastewater, and food waste.
An infrastructure refers to facilities, services, or systems for participations to function.
The type of an actor, e.g. the type of company, or a specific subtype based on the organisations capabilities.
Energy is an ability or a property of matter or a system, to do work because of its motion, its mass, its electric charge, etc.

A role that an actor can take in a specific context. Applies both to roles in the context of resources, such as owner, manufacturer, reseller etc. of that resource, as well as roles in relation to a circular value network, such as recycler, dismantler, transporter etc., in relation to a material flow.

comment.en: A matter is a physical substance.

comment.undefined: Biomass represents matter from recently living (but now dead) organisms such as plants, algae and animals.
The relation representing the particpation of an energy as a resource.

comment.en: A resource able to be handled in the context of a circular value network, e.g. data generated by software systems in the CVN, materials or prooducts as physical objects handled in the CVN.
A physical object is a collection of matter.

comment.undefined: An agent able to act in the context of a circular value network, e.g. an organisation, person.
The type of the actor.
The point in time when something took place or was valid.
Relates some properties to the capability, such as the parameters of it, or the needed resources.
The end of a time interval.
Relates to the actor holding the capability.

label.undefined: hasSustainability measures how sustainable an energy source is.

comment.undefined: Participating object in a resource participation. This is part of a resource participation that can be a directional relation, and the participating object is the end point of the relation.

comment.en: batchSize intends to repsent how many physical objects are belong to a batch of objects.
hasMatter intends to represent that a physical object can have a collection of matter.

comment.undefined: hasConvertedEnergy represents that an energy transformation process has its final energy.
The resource that this participation relation relates to, i.e. for which the actor holds the specified role.
hasEnergyComponentPercentage represents the percentage of a particular energy as a composition.

Relates a thing, e.g. a digital object, or a physical object, to the information it is a realization of. C.f. a physical book that is the realization of a novel, or a pdf or Excel-file that is a realization of a certain data sheet.
The collaboration or process that this participation relates to.
Indicating that something is part of or is contained by something else.

comment.en: hasConstitutent intends to represent that a physical object can have a collection of composing components.

comment.undefined: Holds the value of the role of the participant in this participation relation.
Holds the value of the infrastructure involved in this participation relation.
participatingEnergy represents the energy in an energy composition.
hasOriginalEnergy represents that an energy transformation process has its initial energy.
hasCarbonIntensity measures how intensive that the carbon is for an energy source.
Connecting the information to the object (physical, virtual, imaginary) that the information is about.
hasEnergySource represents that energy can have some energy sources.

comment.en: hasBatch intends to represent that a set of objects can be captured by a number of batches where each batch contains a number of physical objects.

comment.undefined: Participating subject in a resource participation. This is part of a resource participation that can be a directional relation, and the participating subject is the starting point of the relation.
Defines the location of a resource.
Holds the value of the actor involved in this participation relation.
An actor participates in a collaboration based on that it has some capability that is useful for the collaboration.
hasAnergy represents that energy has part of anergy.
Indicating that some piece of information is contained in a larger collection of information, e.g. a data sheet contains a statement about a certain parameter of a product.
The start of a time interval.
hasExergy represents that energy has part of exergy.

comment.en: hasPhysicalObject intends to represent that a batch of objects or a set of objects can have composing components of physical objects.
